Determine the output of the following code:

```java
public class Counter {
    private int count;

    public Counter(int count) {
        this.count = count;
    }

    public void add(int count) {
        this.count += count;
    }

    public int getCount() { return count; }
}
```

```java
Counter c = new Counter(10);
c.add(5);
c.add(3);
System.out.println(c.getCount());
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
public class Wallet {
    private int dollars;

    public Wallet(int dollars) {
        this.dollars = dollars;
    }

    public void transfer(Wallet other) {
        other.dollars += this.dollars;
        this.dollars = 0;
    }

    public int getDollars() { return dollars; }
}
```

```java
Wallet w1 = new Wallet(50);
Wallet w2 = new Wallet(20);
w1.transfer(w2);
System.out.println(w1.getDollars() + " " + w2.getDollars());
```

Consider the following class:

```java
public class Circle {
    private double radius;

    public Circle(double radius) {
        this.radius = radius;
    }

    public boolean isBiggerThan(Circle other) {
        return this.radius > other.radius;
    }
}
```

After the following code executes:

```java
