Circle c2 = new Circle(3.0);
boolean result = c2.isBiggerThan(c1);
```

What is the value of `result`?

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
public class Player {
    private int score;

    public Player(int score) {
        this.score = score;
    }

    public void combine(Player other) {
        this.score += other.score;
        other.score = 0;
    }

    public int getScore() { return score; }
}
```

```java
Player p1 = new Player(30);
Player p2 = new Player(40);
p1.combine(p2);
p2.combine(p1);
System.out.println(p1.getScore() + " " + p2.getScore());
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
public class BankAccount {
    private int balance;

    public BankAccount(int balance) {
        this.balance = balance;
    }

    public void deposit(int balance) {
        this.balance += balance;
    }

    public void merge(BankAccount other) {
        this.deposit(other.balance);
        other.balance = 0;
    }

    public String toString() {
        return "" + balance;
    }
}
```

```java
BankAccount a = new BankAccount(100);
BankAccount b = new BankAccount(200);
a.merge(b);
System.out.println(a + " " + b);
```

Consider the following class.

```java
public class Box {
    private int size;

    public Box(int size) {
        this.size = size * 2;
    }

    public void expand(int size) {
        size = this.size + size;
    }

    public int getSize() { return size; }
}
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
Box b = new Box(4);
b.expand(3);
System.out.println(b.getSize());
```

Consider the following class.

```java
public class Sensor {
    private int reading;

    public Sensor(int reading) {
        this.reading = reading;
    }

    public void calibrate(Sensor other) {
        this.reading = other.reading + 10;
    }

    public void selfCalibrate() {
        calibrate(this);
    }

    public int getReading() { return reading; }
}
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
Sensor s = new Sensor(20);
s.selfCalibrate();
System.out.println(s.getReading());
```

Consider the following class.

```java
public class Point {
    private int x;
    private int y;

    public Point(int x, int y) {
        this.x = x;
        this.y = y;
    }

    public void shift(int x, int y) {
        this.x += x;
        this.y += y;
    }

    public String toString() {
        return x + "," + y;
    }
}
```

Determine the output of the following code segment.

```java
